      "message": "That doesn't sound quite right.  Intel has the copyright for 2017; that hasn't changed, so it seems that \"2017\" still needs to be part of the copyright for Intel.  So which of these is right (or should it be something else):\n\nApproach #1 (this matches what has been done in the past, though may be incorrect)\n2017 Intel\n2018 AT&T\n\nApproach #2 (seems incorrect to me, as it loses the 2017 for Intel)\n2018 Intel, AT&T\n\nApproach #2 (seems incorrect to me, as 2017 doesn't apply to AT&T)\n2017-2018 Intel, AT&T\n\nApproach #3\n2017-2018 Intel\n2018 AT&T",
